name: NSUserActivity.TypedPayloadError
desc: An enumeration that describes the error types for getting and setting a typed payload.

items.name: case encodingError
items.desc: An encoding error that indicates that the content failed to encode into a valid dictionary.

items.name: case invalidContent
items.desc: A decoding error that indicates that the user info dictionary is empty or invalid.

items.name: static func == (NSUserActivity.TypedPayloadError, NSUserActivity.TypedPayloadError) -> Bool
items.desc: An operator for checking whether two typed payload errors are equal.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the essential components of the typed payload error by feeding them into the hasher.
